    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="title">üõ∞Ô∏è Remote Sensing Workflow - Complete Overview</h1>
        
        <div class="workflow">
            <!-- Phase 1: Energy Source & Sensors -->
            <div class="phase phase-1">
                <div class="phase-title">
                    <div class="phase-number">1</div>
                    Energy Source & Sensor Systems
                </div>
                <div class="data-flow">
                    <div class="flow-item">Energy Source</div>
                    <div class="flow-arrow">‚Üí</div>
                    <div class="flow-item">Sensor Detection</div>
                    <div class="flow-arrow">‚Üí</div>
                    <div class="flow-item">Signal Conversion</div>
                </div>
                <div class="components">
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon sensor-icon">‚òÄÔ∏è</div>
                            Energy Sources
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Passive:</strong> Solar radiation, thermal emission<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Active:</strong> Radar (SAR), LiDAR, sonar<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Electromagnetic spectrum:</strong> Visible, NIR, SWIR, thermal, microwave
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon sensor-icon">üì°</div>
                            Sensor Types
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Optical:</strong> Multispectral, hyperspectral<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Thermal:</strong> LWIR, MWIR sensors<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Microwave:</strong> SAR, scatterometers<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>LiDAR:</strong> Bathymetric, topographic
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon sensor-icon">‚ö°</div>
                            Signal Characteristics
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Spectral resolution:</strong> Bandwidth of channels<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Spatial resolution:</strong> Ground sampling distance<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Temporal resolution:</strong> Revisit frequency<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Radiometric resolution:</strong> Bit depth
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step-explanation">
                    <h4><span class="what-icon">WHAT</span> What This Step Does:</h4>
                    <p>This is where it all begins! Energy (like sunlight) hits objects on Earth, and sensors detect the reflected or emitted energy. Think of it like taking a photo, but instead of just visible light, we capture many different types of energy that our eyes can't see - like heat or radar waves.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="connection-box">
                    <h5><span class="connection-icon">‚Üí</span> How it connects to the next step:</h5>
                    <p>The sensors need to be carried on something to get a good view! Raw energy signals are captured and need a platform (satellite, plane, or drone) to position the sensors properly and collect this data systematically.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="arrow">‚Üì</div>

            <!-- Phase 2: Platform Systems -->
            <div class="phase phase-2">
                <div class="phase-title">
                    <div class="phase-number">2</div>
                    Platform & Data Acquisition
                </div>
                <div class="components">
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon platform-icon">üõ∞Ô∏è</div>
                            Satellite Platforms
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>LEO:</strong> Landsat, Sentinel, MODIS<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>GEO:</strong> GOES, Meteosat<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Sun-synchronous:</strong> Consistent lighting<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Polar orbiting:</strong> Global coverage
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon platform-icon">‚úàÔ∏è</div>
                            Airborne Platforms
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Aircraft:</strong> High spatial resolution<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>UAV/Drones:</strong> Flexible, low-cost<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Helicopters:</strong> Hovering capability<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Balloons:</strong> Long endurance
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon platform-icon">üöÅ</div>
                            Ground-based Systems
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Towers:</strong> Continuous monitoring<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Mobile units:</strong> Field campaigns<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Handheld:</strong> Field spectroradiometers<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Fixed stations:</strong> Weather, flux towers
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="key-points">
                    <h4>Key Acquisition Parameters:</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Orbital mechanics and viewing geometry</li>
                        <li>Atmospheric conditions and timing</li>
                        <li>Platform stability and navigation</li>
                        <li>Data downlink and storage systems</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step-explanation">
                    <h4><span class="what-icon">WHAT</span> What This Step Does:</h4>
                    <p>Now we put our sensors on vehicles! Satellites orbit Earth taking pictures regularly, airplanes fly specific routes for detailed coverage, and drones can hover over small areas. Each platform has advantages - satellites see the whole world but less detail, while drones see tiny areas in great detail.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="connection-box">
                    <h5><span class="connection-icon">‚Üí</span> How it connects to the next step:</h5>
                    <p>The raw data collected from space or air is messy and distorted (like a photo taken through a dirty, curved window). This raw data needs to be cleaned up and corrected before we can actually use it for analysis.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="arrow">‚Üì</div>

            <!-- Phase 3: Data Processing -->
            <div class="phase phase-3">
                <div class="phase-title">
                    <div class="phase-number">3</div>
                    Data Processing & Correction
                </div>
                <div class="data-flow">
                    <div class="flow-item">Raw Data</div>
                    <div class="flow-arrow">‚Üí</div>
                    <div class="flow-item">Preprocessing</div>
                    <div class="flow-arrow">‚Üí</div>
                    <div class="flow-item">Corrections</div>
                    <div class="flow-arrow">‚Üí</div>
                    <div class="flow-item">Enhanced Data</div>
                </div>
                <div class="components">
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon processing-icon">üîß</div>
                            Preprocessing
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Radiometric:</strong> DN to radiance/reflectance<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Geometric:</strong> Orthorectification, geocoding<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Atmospheric:</strong> Scattering, absorption correction<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Topographic:</strong> Slope/aspect normalization
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon processing-icon">üåü</div>
                            Enhancement
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Spatial:</strong> Filtering, sharpening, fusion<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Spectral:</strong> Band ratios, transformations<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Temporal:</strong> Compositing, gap filling<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Noise reduction:</strong> Destriping, smoothing
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon processing-icon">üîÑ</div>
                            Transformations
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>PCA:</strong> Dimensionality reduction<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Tasseled Cap:</strong> Vegetation indices<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Fourier:</strong> Frequency domain analysis<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Wavelet:</strong> Multi-resolution analysis
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step-explanation">
                    <h4><span class="what-icon">WHAT</span> What This Step Does:</h4>
                    <p>This is like developing a film photograph or editing a digital photo. The raw data is corrected for problems like atmospheric haze, camera distortions, and lighting differences. We also enhance the images to make features more visible and align them properly with maps.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="connection-box">
                    <h5><span class="connection-icon">‚Üí</span> How it connects to the next step:</h5>
                    <p>Now that we have clean, corrected images, we can start asking questions! "What is this green area - forest or farmland?" "How much has this city grown?" The processed data is ready for analysis to extract meaningful information.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="arrow">‚Üì</div>

            <!-- Phase 4: Analysis & Interpretation -->
            <div class="phase phase-4">
                <div class="phase-title">
                    <div class="phase-number">4</div>
                    Analysis & Information Extraction
                </div>
                <div class="components">
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon analysis-icon">üîç</div>
                            Image Classification
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Supervised:</strong> Maximum likelihood, SVM, RF<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Unsupervised:</strong> K-means, ISODATA<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Object-based:</strong> OBIA, segmentation<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Deep learning:</strong> CNNs, semantic segmentation
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon analysis-icon">üìä</div>
                            Feature Extraction
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Spectral indices:</strong> NDVI, EVI, NDWI<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Texture analysis:</strong> GLCM, wavelets<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Shape metrics:</strong> Area, perimeter, compactness<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Temporal features:</strong> Phenology, trends
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon analysis-icon">üéØ</div>
                            Change Detection
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Pixel-based:</strong> Image differencing, ratios<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Object-based:</strong> Segmentation comparison<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Time series:</strong> Trend analysis, breakpoints<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Machine learning:</strong> Change vector analysis
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon analysis-icon">üß†</div>
                            Advanced Analytics
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Machine learning:</strong> Regression, clustering<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Deep learning:</strong> Neural networks, AutoML<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Time series:</strong> Harmonic analysis, BFAST<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Fusion:</strong> Multi-sensor data integration
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step-explanation">
                    <h4><span class="what-icon">WHAT</span> What This Step Does:</h4>
                    <p>This is the detective work! We teach computers to recognize patterns and classify what they see. "This red signature is a roof, this green is healthy vegetation, this brown is bare soil." We can also track changes over time, like watching a forest disappear or a city expand.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="connection-box">
                    <h5><span class="connection-icon">‚Üí</span> How it connects to the next step:</h5>
                    <p>But wait - how do we know our computer got it right? We need to check our work! The analysis results need to be validated against real-world truth to make sure they're accurate and reliable.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="arrow">‚Üì</div>

            <!-- Phase 5: Validation & Quality Assessment -->
            <div class="phase phase-5">
                <div class="phase-title">
                    <div class="phase-number">5</div>
                    Validation & Quality Assessment
                </div>
                <div class="components">
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon validation-icon">‚úÖ</div>
                            Ground Truth Collection
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Field surveys:</strong> GPS, sampling protocols<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Reference datasets:</strong> Higher resolution imagery<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>In-situ measurements:</strong> Instruments, sensors<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Existing databases:</strong> Land cover, inventory data
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon validation-icon">üìà</div>
                            Accuracy Assessment
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Confusion matrix:</strong> Producer's/user's accuracy<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Statistical measures:</strong> Kappa, F1-score<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Cross-validation:</strong> K-fold, leave-one-out<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Spatial validation:</strong> Moran's I, variograms
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="component">
                        <div class="component-title">
                            <div class="icon validation-icon">üî¨</div>
                            Quality Control
                        </div>
                        <div class="component-details">
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Metadata:</strong> Processing history, lineage<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Uncertainty:</strong> Error propagation, confidence<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Consistency:</strong> Temporal, spatial coherence<br>
                            ‚Ä¢ <strong>Standards:</strong> ISO, FGDC compliance
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="step-explanation">
                    <h4><span class="what-icon">WHAT</span> What This Step Does:</h4>
                    <p>Quality control time! We send people to the field with GPS units to check "Did the computer correctly identify this as farmland?" We compare our results with known reference data and calculate accuracy percentages. This is like having a teacher grade our homework.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="connection-box">
                    <h5><span class="connection-icon">‚Üí</span> How it connects to the next step:</h5>
                    <p>Once we know our results are accurate and reliable, we can confidently use them for real-world decisions! The validated information becomes useful products that help solve actual problems.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="arrow">‚Üì</div>

